        "## **Question 1:** Create an object named student with the following properties:\n",
        "- name: \"Rahul\"\n",
        "- age: 21\n",
        "- courses: an array containing \"Math\", \"Physics\", and \"Chemistry\"\n",
        "\n",
        "Then, perform the following operations:\n",
        "1. Add a new property grade with the value \"A\".\n",
        "2. Update the age to 22.\n",
        "3. Delete the courses property.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Add property:** `student.grade = \"A\"` â€” dot notation assigns a new key-value pair dynamically.\n",
        "- **Update property:** `student.age = 22` â€” same syntax, just overwrites the existing value.\n",
        "- **Delete property:** `delete student.courses` â€” removes the key and its value entirely from the object.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "3a87fc61",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3a87fc61"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "// Create the student object\n",
        "const student = {\n",
        "  name: \"Rahul\",\n",
        "  age: 21,\n",
        "  courses: [\"Math\", \"Physics\", \"Chemistry\"]\n",
        "};\n",
        "console.log(\"Original:\", JSON.stringify(student));\n",
        "\n",
        "// 1. Add a new property 'grade'\n",
        "student.grade = \"A\";\n",
        "console.log(\"After adding grade:\", JSON.stringify(student));\n",
        "\n",
        "// 2. Update age to 22\n",
        "student.age = 22;\n",
        "console.log(\"After updating age:\", JSON.stringify(student));\n",
        "\n",
        "// 3. Delete the courses property\n",
        "delete student.courses;\n",
        "console.log(\"After deleting courses:\", JSON.stringify(student));\n"
      ]
    },
