        "## **Question 2:** Write a function checkEligibility that takes an age as a parameter and returns:\n",
        "- `Eligible` if age is 18 or above\n",
        "- `Not Eligible` if age is below 18\n",
        "\n",
        "Use an if-else statement.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "951b7758",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "951b7758"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "function checkEligibility(age) {\n",
        "  if (age >= 18) {\n",
        "    return \"Eligible\";\n",
        "  } else {\n",
        "    return \"Not Eligible\";\n",
        "  }\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "// Test cases\n",
        "console.log(checkEligibility(20));  // Eligible\n",
        "console.log(checkEligibility(17));  // Not Eligible\n",
        "console.log(checkEligibility(18));  // Eligible (boundary case)\n"
      ]
    },
