      },
      "source": [
        "## **Question 3:** Write a function `getDayName` that takes a number (1â€“7) and returns the corresponding day of the week. Use a `switch` statement.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "`switch` compares the expression against each `case` value using strict equality (`===`).  \n",
        "`break` stops execution from falling through to the next case.  \n",
        "`default` handles any value that doesn't match a case.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "749c39dc",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "749c39dc"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "function getDayName(num) {\n",
        "  switch (num) {\n",
        "    case 1: return \"Monday\";\n",
        "    case 2: return \"Tuesday\";\n",
        "    case 3: return \"Wednesday\";\n",
        "    case 4: return \"Thursday\";\n",
        "    case 5: return \"Friday\";\n",
        "    case 6: return \"Saturday\";\n",
        "    case 7: return \"Sunday\";\n",
        "    default: return \"Invalid day number (must be 1â€“7)\";\n",
        "  }\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "// Test all 7 days\n",
        "for (let i = 1; i <= 7; i++) {\n",
        "  console.log(`Day ${i}: ${getDayName(i)}`);\n",
        "}\n",
        "console.log(getDayName(9));  // Invalid\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
