      "source": [
        "## **Question 4:** Rewrite the `checkEligibility` function from Question 2 using the **ternary operator**.\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "The ternary operator is a concise one-liner:  `condition ? valueIfTrue : valueIfFalse`\n",
        "\n",
        "It replaces a simple `if-else` that returns one of two values.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "6076d073",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6076d073"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "// Ternary version â€” same logic, one line\n",
        "function checkEligibility(age) {\n",
        "  return age >= 18 ? \"Eligible\" : \"Not Eligible\";\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "console.log(checkEligibility(20));  // Eligible\n",
        "console.log(checkEligibility(15));  // Not Eligible\n",
        "console.log(checkEligibility(18));  // Eligible\n",
        "\n",
        "// Can also write as an arrow function with ternary (bonus):\n",
        "const checkEligibilityArrow = age => age >= 18 ? \"Eligible\" : \"Not Eligible\";\n",
        "console.log(\"\\nArrow version:\", checkEligibilityArrow(21));\n"
      ]
    },
