      },
      "source": [
        "## **Question 5:** Given an array numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], perform the following:\n",
        "1. Use a for loop to print each number.\n",
        "2. Use a while loop to print each number.\n",
        "3. Use a for-in loop to print each index.\n",
        "4. Use a for-of loop to print each number.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "| Loop | Best used for |\n",
        "|------|--------------|\n",
        "| `for` | When you need the index and full control |\n",
        "| `while` | When the number of iterations isn't known upfront |\n",
        "| `for-in` | Iterating over **keys/indices** of an object or array |\n",
        "| `for-of` | Iterating over **values** of an iterable (arrays, strings) |\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "7e8d6788",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7e8d6788"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];\n",
        "\n",
        "// 1. for loop â€” classic index-based\n",
        "console.log(\"=== for loop ===\");\n",
        "for (let i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {\n",
        "  console.log(numbers[i]);\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "// 2. while loop\n",
        "console.log(\"=== while loop ===\");\n",
        "let i = 0;\n",
        "while (i < numbers.length) {\n",
        "  console.log(numbers[i]);\n",
        "  i++;\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "// 3. for-in loop â€” prints indices (keys)\n",
        "console.log(\"=== for-in loop (indices) ===\");\n",
        "for (let index in numbers) {\n",
        "  console.log(\"Index:\", index);\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "// 4. for-of loop â€” prints values directly\n",
        "console.log(\"=== for-of loop ===\");\n",
        "for (let num of numbers) {\n",
        "  console.log(num);\n",
        "}\n"
      ]
    },
