        "## Question 6\n",
        "Explain what functions are in JavaScript and provide an example of a function that adds two numbers.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "A **function** is a reusable block of code that performs a specific task. It can accept **parameters** (inputs), execute a body of code, and **return** a value (output). Functions help avoid repetition (DRY â€” Don't Repeat Yourself) and keep code organised.\n",
        "\n",
        "JavaScript has three main ways to declare a function:\n",
        "- **Function Declaration** â€” `function name() {}`  (hoisted)\n",
        "- **Function Expression** â€” `const name = function() {}`  (not hoisted)\n",
        "- **Arrow Function** â€” `const name = () => {}`  (compact syntax, ES6)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "dae740f5",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dae740f5"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "// Function Declaration\n",
        "function add(a, b) {\n",
        "  return a + b;\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "console.log(\"add(3, 5) =\", add(3, 5));   // 8\n",
        "console.log(\"add(10, 20) =\", add(10, 20)); // 30\n",
        "console.log(\"add(-4, 9) =\", add(-4, 9));  // 5\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "9c1c5954",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9c1c5954"
      },
      "source": [
        "## **Question 7:** Convert the `add` function from Qurstion-6 into an **arrow function**.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "Arrow functions (`=>`) are a shorter ES6 syntax. When the function body is a single `return` expression, curly braces and the `return` keyword can both be dropped (implicit return).\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "a86dd005",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a86dd005"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "// Full arrow function syntax\n",
        "const add = (a, b) => {\n",
        "  return a + b;\n",
        "};\n",
        "\n",
        "// Concise (implicit return) â€” same result, one line\n",
        "const addConcise = (a, b) => a + b;\n",
        "\n",
        "console.log(\"Full arrow:    add(4, 6) =\", add(4, 6));         // 10\n",
        "console.log(\"Concise arrow: addConcise(4, 6) =\", addConcise(4, 6)); // 10\n",
        "\n",
        "// Single parameter â€” parentheses optional\n",
        "const double = n => n * 2;\n",
        "console.log(\"double(7) =\", double(7));  // 14\n"
      ]
    },
    {
