        "## **Question 8:** Write a function `greet` that takes a `name` and a `callback` function. The `greet` function should call the callback with the name.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "A **callback** is a function passed as an argument to another function and invoked inside it. This is a core pattern in JavaScript used for event handling, timers, and asynchronous operations.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "533fb760",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "533fb760"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "// greet accepts a name and a callback, then invokes the callback with the name\n",
        "function greet(name, callback) {\n",
        "  callback(name);\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "// Example callback 1 â€” formal greeting\n",
        "function formalGreeting(name) {\n",
        "  console.log(\"Good day, \" + name + \"!\");\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "// Example callback 2 â€” casual greeting (arrow function)\n",
        "const casualGreeting = name => console.log(\"Hey \" + name + \"! đź‘‹\");\n",
        "\n",
        "greet(\"Priya\", formalGreeting);\n",
        "greet(\"Aryan\", casualGreeting);\n"
      ]
    },
