        "## **Question 9:** Given the Array:\n",
        " `const fruits = [\"apple\", \"banana\", \"cherry\"]`:\n",
        "1. What is the length of the array?\n",
        "2. Add `\"date\"` to the end of the array using the `length` property.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- `array.length` returns the number of elements.\n",
        "- `array[array.length] = value` is equivalent to `array.push(value)` â€” it writes to the next available index.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "0ac34cbd",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0ac34cbd"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "const fruits = [\"apple\", \"banana\", \"cherry\"];\n",
        "\n",
        "// 1. Length of the array\n",
        "console.log(\"Length:\", fruits.length);  // 3\n",
        "\n",
        "// 2. Add \"date\" using the length property as the new index\n",
        "fruits[fruits.length] = \"date\";\n",
        "\n",
        "console.log(\"After adding 'date':\", fruits);       // [\"apple\", \"banana\", \"cherry\", \"date\"]\n",
        "console.log(\"New length:\", fruits.length);          // 4\n",
        "\n",
        "// Note: push() is the more common way to do the same thing:\n",
        "// fruits.push(\"date\");\n"
      ]
    },
