        "## **Question 10:** Given the string `text = \" Hello World! \"`, perform the following:\n",
        "1. Trim the whitespace\n",
        "2. Convert to uppercase\n",
        "3. Check if it includes `\"World\"`\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "| Method | What it does |\n",
        "|--------|-------------|\n",
        "| `.trim()` | Removes leading and trailing whitespace |\n",
        "| `.toUpperCase()` | Returns a new string with all letters uppercased |\n",
        "| `.includes(str)` | Returns `true` if the string contains `str`, else `false` |\n",
        "\n",
        "> Strings in JavaScript are **immutable** â€” these methods return new strings, the original is unchanged.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "3ca7434d",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3ca7434d"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "const text = \" Hello World! \";\n",
        "console.log(\"Original:  '\" + text + \"'\");\n",
        "\n",
        "// 1. Trim whitespace\n",
        "const trimmed = text.trim();\n",
        "console.log(\"Trimmed:   '\" + trimmed + \"'\");      // 'Hello World!'\n",
        "\n",
        "// 2. Convert to uppercase\n",
        "const upper = trimmed.toUpperCase();\n",
        "console.log(\"Uppercase: '\" + upper + \"'\");         // 'HELLO WORLD!'\n",
        "\n",
        "// 3. Check if it includes \"World\"\n",
        "const hasWorld = text.includes(\"World\");\n",
        "console.log('Includes \"World\":', hasWorld);         // true\n",
        "\n",
        "// Chain all three in one expression:\n",
        "console.log(\"\\nChained:\", text.trim().toUpperCase().includes(\"WORLD\")); // true\n"
      ]
    },
