        "## **Question 11:** Given the array numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], perform the following:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Add `6` to the end\n",
        "2. Remove the first element\n",
        "3. Find the index of `4`\n",
        "4. Check if all numbers are greater than `0`\n",
        "\n",
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "| Method | What it does | Returns |\n",
        "|--------|-------------|---------|\n",
        "| `.push(val)` | Adds element to the **end** | New length |\n",
        "| `.shift()` | Removes element from the **front** | Removed element |\n",
        "| `.indexOf(val)` | Finds first index of a value | Index or `-1` |\n",
        "| `.every(fn)` | Tests if **all** elements pass a condition | `true` / `false` |\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "604c246b",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "604c246b"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%%javascript\n",
        "let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];\n",
        "console.log(\"Original:\", numbers);\n",
        "\n",
        "// 1. Add 6 to the end using push()\n",
        "numbers.push(6);\n",
        "console.log(\"After push(6):\", numbers);          // [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]\n",
        "\n",
        "// 2. Remove the first element using shift()\n",
        "const removed = numbers.shift();\n",
        "console.log(\"Removed element:\", removed);         // 1\n",
        "console.log(\"After shift():\", numbers);           // [2, 3, 4, 5, 6]\n",
        "\n",
        "// 3. Find the index of 4\n",
        "const idx = numbers.indexOf(4);\n",
        "console.log(\"Index of 4:\", idx);                  // 2  (0-based after shift)\n",
        "\n",
        "// 4. Check if ALL numbers are greater than 0\n",
        "const allPositive = numbers.every(n => n > 0);\n",
        "console.log(\"All > 0:\", allPositive);             // true\n",
        "\n",
        "// Bonus â€” test with a negative number\n",
        "const mixed = [2, 3, -1, 5];\n",
        "console.log(\"All > 0 in [2,3,-1,5]:\", mixed.every(n => n > 0)); // false\n"
      ]
    }
